org.gridgain.grid.spi.discovery.tcp.ipfinder.s3
Class GridTcpDiscoveryS3IpFinder

java.lang.Object

      org.gridgain.grid.spi.discovery.tcp.ipfinder.s3.GridTcpDiscoveryS3IpFinder
All Implemented Interfaces:
GridTcpDiscoveryIpFinder, GridSpiCloseable
public class GridTcpDiscoveryS3IpFinder
extends GridTcpDiscoveryIpFinderAdapter

AWS S3-based IP finder.

For information about Amazon S3 visit aws.amazon.com.

Configuration

Mandatory

  • AWS credentials (see GridTcpDiscoveryS3IpFinder.setAwsCredentials(AWSCredentials))

Optional

  • Client configuration (see GridTcpDiscoveryS3IpFinder.setClientConfiguration(ClientConfiguration))
  • Bucket name suffix (see GridTcpDiscoveryS3IpFinder.setBucketNameSuffix(String))
  • Shared flag (see GridTcpDiscoveryIpFinderAdapter.setShared(boolean))

The finder will create S3 bucket. The name is built in the following way: GridTcpDiscoveryS3IpFinder.BUCKET_NAME_PREFIX + suffix provided by user (see GridTcpDiscoveryS3IpFinder.setBucketNameSuffix(String)). If suffix is not provided by user, then GridTcpDiscoveryS3IpFinder.DFLT_BUCKET_NAME_SUFFIX is used.

The bucket will contain one-byte-length entries named like the following 192.168.1.136#1001.

Note that storing data in AWS S3 service will result in charges to your AWS account. Choose another implementation of GridTcpDiscoveryIpFinder for local or home network tests.

Note that this finder is shared by default (see GridTcpDiscoveryIpFinder.isShared().
